properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 3:57AM CST until January 11 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Winter Storm This Afternoon into Late Saturday...

.A large low pressure system will affect Iowa to end the week
spreading two episodes of wintry precipitation across the state.
The first push should bring snow and blowing snow through central
sections with freezing rain and a wintry mix south this
afternoon, both lasting into at least the evening hours. The
second push Saturday into the early evening hours east will
mainly be snow and blowing snow. Moderate to heavy snow
storm total accumulations are expected over the southeast two-
thirds of Iowa by the time the storm ends Saturday evening.

* WHAT...Moderate snow. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches
and ice accumulations of a light glaze south. Winds gusting as
high as 35 mph later today.

* WHERE...Central and southwest Iowa.

* WHEN...From noon today to 6 AM CST Saturday. Snow mainly in two
episodes, this afternoon and this evening, and again Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 6 AM CST SATURDAY
